 The completed work was primarily theoretical in nature, but the program was written for the simulation of observations of the Sagittarius Galaxy.
 The team was looking for the effect that would be caused by the tidal forces between the dark matter of the universe and that of the Milky Way.
 Similar to how the moon exerts force on the earth, which leads to tides, the Milky Way exerts force on the Sagittarius Galaxy.
 The researchers concluded that dark matter affects other dark matter in the same way as ordinary matter.
 According to this theory, most of the dark matter in a galaxy is located in a ring around it, and is made up of a large number of smaller particles.
