 In urine samples from pets that died after eating contaminated pet food, both cyanuric acid and melamine were found.
 Researchers at the University have found that the two compounds react with each other, forming crystals that can block kidney function.
 Scientists discovered that crystals are formed in cat urine when you add melanin and cyanuric acid.
 The composition of these crystals has similarities with that of the urine of the affected pets, compared with infrared spectroscopy (FTIR).
