 In the cities of Harappa and Mohenjodaro, almost every house had a flush toilet connected to an advanced sewage system.
 Sewage remains have been found in houses in the Minoan cities on the Greek islands of Crete and Santorini.
 There were also toilets in China, Egypt and Persia in ancient times. Toilets in the Roman era were often part of a public bathhouse, where both men and women gathered in a mixed group.
 When you call someone who is thousands of miles away, you are using a satellite.
 As soon as the spacecraft receives the call, it immediately sends it back.
 The satellite is shot into space by a rocket. Scientists use telescopes in space because the earth's atmosphere distorts some of our light and images.
 To launch a satellite or telescope into space, you need a huge rocket that is more than 30 meters long.
