 After watching the movie National Treasure, you might think that there is a treasure map hidden behind the Declaration of Independence.
 However, this is a misconception. There is something written on the back, but it is not a treasure map.
 On the back of the American Declaration of Independence are the words 'Original Declaration of Independence, July 4, 1776'. The text is upside down at the bottom of the document.
 Although no one knows for sure who wrote it, it is certain that the large parchment (29¾ inches by 24½ inches) was once rolled up for storage.
 So it seems that the designation was simply added as a kind of label.
