 Muhammad was intensely concerned with matters of the spirit. He often went to a cave for meditation, which later became known as the Cave of Hira in the mountains of Noer.
 The cave itself, which has withstood the test of time, gives a very vivid picture of the spirituality of Muhammad.
 The cave is located on one of the mountain tops on the north side of Mecca and is completely closed off from the rest of the world.
 Even though it was known that the cave existed, it was not easy to find. Once inside the cave, there is total isolation.
 All you can see is the clear, beautiful sky and the many surrounding mountains. From the cave, you can see very little of the world.
 The Great Pyramid of Giza is the only one of the Seven Wonders of the Ancient World that still stands.
 The Great Pyramid was built by the Egyptians in the third century B.C. and is one of the many large pyramid structures built in honor of a deceased pharaoh.
 The Giza Plateau or 'Pyramids of Giza' in the Egyptian Valley of the Kings contains several pyramids (with the Great Pyramid being the largest), several smaller tombs, a number of temples and the Great Sphinx.
 The Great Pyramid was built to honor Pharaoh Khufu. Many of the smaller pyramids, tombs, and temples were built as tributes to Khufu's wives and family members.
 The up-bow sign looks like a V and the down-bow sign looks like a dot or a square with the bottom missing.
 Above means that you should start at the tip and push the iron away. Below means that you should start at the bow (the place where your hand holds the iron) and pull the iron.
 An upward movement usually produces a softer sound, while a downward movement produces a stronger and more assertive sound.
 Take the liberty to sketch your personal signs, but do not forget that the printed staff signs are there for a musical reason, so they should mostly be respected.
