 Tibetan Buddhism consists of a relatively simple core of kundalini yoga, meditation, and a following of universal love.
 Through yoga postures, breathing exercises, mantras and visualized images, the energy of Kundalini yoga (enlightenment energy) is awakened.
 The core of Tibetan meditation is yoga with a deity as a focus. With the help of the visualization of different deities, energy channels are cleared, chakras are activated and the consciousness is brought into an enlightened state.
