 In physiological and behavioral rhythm observations, there is often a strong dependence on endogenous processes and the production via the biological clock.
 Most organisms, including bacteria, fungi, plants and animals, live according to periodic rhythms. These are not just reactions to external periodic signals.
 Biological clocks are self-sustaining oscillators that go through a cycle for a certain period of time, even if there are no external signals for this.
 The experiment of Hershey and Chase was one of the most important indications that DNA was a genetic material.
 Hershey and Chase used bacteriophages or viruses to implant their own DNA into a bacterium.
 Two experiments were performed: in one experiment the DNA in the phage was labelled with a radioactive phosphorus and in the other experiment the protein of the phage was labelled with radioactive sulphur.
 Mutations can have many different effects, depending on the type, the importance of the genetic material involved, and whether the affected cells are stem cells.
 Only mutations in germ cells are heritable. Other mutations can cause cells to die or can cause cancer.
