 Traffic flow is the study of the movements of individual drivers and vehicles between two points and the interactions that take place between the individuals.
 Unfortunately, it is difficult to examine the traffic flow, because the behavior of drivers cannot be predicted with 100% certainty.
 Fortunately, drivers behave reasonably predictably. This means that traffic flows show some degree of consistency and that something can be said about this in mathematical terms.
 There are links between the three core characteristics to better represent traffic flow: (1) intensity, (2) density and (3) speed.
 These relationships facilitate the planning, design and operation of road engineering facilities.
 Insects were the first animals to fly. Thanks to their flying ability, they could more easily escape predators and more efficiently find food and mates.
 The advantage of most insects is that they can fold their wings along the body.
 This allows them to hide in a larger number of small places from predators.
 Currently, only dragonflies and mayflies cannot fold their wings.
