 The Amazon River is the world's largest and second longest river and carries more than 8 times the volume of water as the second largest.
 The Amazon is also the widest river on earth and has a width of six miles in some places.
 At least 20% of all water that flows into the sea via the rivers comes from the Amazon.
 The main stream of the Amazon River is 6,387 kilometres (3,980 mi) long. The water comes from thousands of smaller rivers.
