 Kruger National Park (KNP) is located in the northeast of South Africa and runs in the east along the border with Mozambique, in the north along the border with Zimbabwe and the southern border is the Crocodile River.
 19.500 square kilometres is the size of the park, divided into 14 different eco-zones, where various wild animal species are kept.
 As a major attraction in South Africa, this park is the flagship of the South African National Parks (SANParks).
 As with all South African national parks, daily conservation fees and entrance fees apply.
 It can also be useful to buy a Wild Card. These offer either access to certain parts of South Africa's parks or to all national parks in South Africa.
 The entire territory of Hong Kong is named after the island of Hong Kong and that is considered by many tourists as the main place.
 The skyline of Hong Kong, with its many buildings, has been compared to a glittering bar chart that is visible thanks to the waters of Victoria Harbour.
 For the best view of Hong Kong, leave the island and head to the waterfront of Kowloon across the harbor.
 The vast majority of the population of the island of Hong Kong lives very close together on reclaimed land along the northern coast.
 This is where the British colonists settled, so if you are looking for evidence of the colonial past of the area, then you can start here.
 The Sundarbans are the largest mangrove forests in the world, stretching 80 km (50 miles) from the coast into Indian and Bangladeshi territory.
 The Sundarbans are now officially listed on the UNESCO World Heritage List. The part within the Indian borders is called the Sundarbans National Park.
 The forests, however, are more than just mangrove swamps — they also contain some of the last mighty stretches of jungle that ever covered the Gangetic plain.
 The Sundarbans cover an area of 3,850 km², of which a third is peat and marshland.
 The Sundarbans have been a wildlife sanctuary since 1966, and the area is now home to an estimated 400 Bengal tigers and about 30,000 axis deer.
